Manor Road, at the S. E. corner of Windsor Road. The house is the home of District Attorney Fach of Richmond County and bears street number 663. The house and barns were formerly
part of the Reon Barnes estate.
June 5, 1930
P. L. Sperr

663 Manor Road, east side, 50 yards south of Windsor Road, ahowing the A. C. Fach residence. It was formerly (1898 to 1917 maps)
the Reon Barnes house.
April 22, 1932
P. L. Sperr
